title: Buck Rogers in the 25th century. [Sound recording]
creator: Francisco Cascales
description: Book digitized by Google from the library of Oxford University and uploaded to the Internet Archive by user tpb.
Recorded from broadcasts of the program of the same title

SUMMARY: Presents two episodes from the science fiction adventure featuring Buck Rogers. With the aid of Dr. Huer's electrohypnotic-mentalophone, Buck tells how he was transferred from the 20th to the 25th century. The subsequent episode describes Dr. Huer's gyrocosmic-relativator and its theft by the villans Killer Kane and Ardala Valmar. Includes commercials
